<section>
  <title><literal>Placeholder</literal> markup type</title>
  <para>
    Marks up a substring inside a headword (or inside a headword
    translation) which is not part of the expression itself but stands
    for things that can take its place, or constitutes some kind of
    meta-notation. Examples:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>beat [sb.] up</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>continue [your] studies</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    Markup of:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>headword</literal> property of <literal>Entry</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <literal>text</literal> property of
        <literal>HeadwordTranslation</literal>
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</section>
